Package uma

Interface PracticeDescription

All Superinterfaces:
ContentDescription, Element, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, MethodElement, MethodUnit, NamedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, PackageableElement
All Known Implementing Classes:
PracticeDescriptionImpl
public interface PracticeDescription
extends ContentDescription
A representation of the model object 'Practice Description'.

The following features are supported:

  • Additional Info
  • Problem
  • Background
  • Goals
  • Application
  • Levels Of Adoption
See Also:
UmaPackage.getPracticeDescription()

      java.lang.String getLevelsOfAdoption()
      Returns the value of the 'Levels Of Adoption' attribute. The default value is "". Outlines the different forms or variants in which the practice could be realized. (e.g. full adoption verus a partial adoption of the Practice)
